  "action_title": "Cut and apply herbicide to control bracken",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nOne randomized, controlled study in the UK\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide to control bracken did not alter heather biomass. One randomized, controlled, before-and-after trial in Norway\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide increased heather cover. One\u00a0randomized, replicated, controlled, paired study in the UK found that cutting and using herbicide had no significant effect on the cover of seven plant species.\nOne replicated, randomized, controlled study in the UK\u00a0found that cutting bracken followed by applying herbicide increased plant species richness when compared with applying herbicide followed by cutting.\nThree randomized, controlled studies (one also a before-and-after trial, and one of which was a paired study) in the UK\u00a0and Norway\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide reduced bracken biomass\u00a0or cover."
}

{
  "query": "When trying to control bracken in UK heathlands, how does using herbicide alone compare to cutting, or a combination of both?",
  "relevant_summary": "Studies comparing bracken control methods in UK heathlands show varying effectiveness:\n\nHerbicide alone showed mixed results for heather recovery. One UK study found it increased heather seedlings and biomass, but two randomized controlled studies found it did not increase heather cover. For bracken control, three UK studies found herbicide reduced bracken biomass/cover, though one study found no change in abundance.\n\nCutting alone also produced mixed results. One UK study and one Norwegian trial found cutting increased heather cover/biomass, but two UK studies found no increases in heather cover/seedlings. For bracken reduction, two UK studies and one Norwegian trial found cutting reduced bracken cover/biomass, with one UK study finding mixed effects.\n\nThe combined approach showed more consistent positive outcomes. Studies found cutting plus herbicide reduced bracken biomass/cover and in one Norwegian trial increased heather cover. One UK study found this combination increased plant species richness compared to herbicide followed by cutting, though another study found no effect on seven specific plant species.\n\nFor plant diversity, herbicide alone increased species richness in one study but showed no effect in another. Cutting alone increased species richness in one study and species diversity in another. The combination treatment increased plant species richness compared to some other approaches.",
  "action_ids": [
    "1652",
    "1653",
    "1654"
  ]
}

